.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Message \- Nostr protocol message serialization and parsing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Message;
\&
\&    # Client\-to\-relay: publish an event
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->new(type => \*(AqEVENT\*(Aq, event => $event);
\&    my $json = $msg\->serialize;  # \*(Aq["EVENT",{...}]\*(Aq
\&
\&    # Client\-to\-relay: subscribe
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->new(
\&        type            => \*(AqREQ\*(Aq,
\&        subscription_id => \*(Aqfeed\*(Aq,
\&        filters         => [$filter1, $filter2],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Client\-to\-relay: close subscription
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->new(
\&        type            => \*(AqCLOSE\*(Aq,
\&        subscription_id => \*(Aqfeed\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse a relay EVENT message
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->parse($json_string);
\&    say $msg\->type;             # \*(AqEVENT\*(Aq
\&    say $msg\->subscription_id;  # \*(Aqfeed\*(Aq
\&    say $msg\->event\->content;   # event content
\&
\&    # Client\-to\-relay: NIP\-42 authentication
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->new(type => \*(AqAUTH\*(Aq, event => $auth_event);
\&
\&    # Relay\-to\-client: AUTH challenge
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->parse(\*(Aq["AUTH","challenge\-string"]\*(Aq);
\&    say $msg\->challenge;  # \*(Aqchallenge\-string\*(Aq
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Handles all NIP\-01 message types for both client\-to\-relay and relay\-to\-client
communication. Messages are constructed with \f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR, serialized with
\&\f(CW\*(C`serialize\*(C'\fR, and parsed from JSON with \f(CW\*(C`parse\*(C'\fR.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->new(type => $type, ...);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new message. \f(CW\*(C`type\*(C'\fR is required and must be one of: \f(CW\*(C`EVENT\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`REQ\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`CLOSE\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`OK\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`EOSE\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`NOTICE\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`CLOSED\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`COUNT\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`AUTH\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`NEG\-OPEN\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`NEG\-MSG\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`NEG\-CLOSE\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`NEG\-ERR\*(C'\fR.
.PP
Required fields by type:
.PP
.Vb 10
\&    EVENT  \- event (Net::Nostr::Event object), optional subscription_id
\&    REQ    \- subscription_id, filters (arrayref of Net::Nostr::Filter)
\&    CLOSE  \- subscription_id
\&    OK     \- event_id (64\-char lowercase hex), accepted (bool), optional message (defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq)
\&    EOSE   \- subscription_id
\&    NOTICE \- message (string)
\&    CLOSED \- subscription_id, message (string)
\&    COUNT     \- subscription_id, filters (client\-to\-relay) or count (non\-negative integer, relay\-to\-client); mutually exclusive
\&    AUTH       \- challenge (string) or event (Net::Nostr::Event object); mutually exclusive
\&    NEG\-OPEN  \- subscription_id, filter (Net::Nostr::Filter), neg_msg (hex string)
\&    NEG\-MSG   \- subscription_id, neg_msg (hex string)
\&    NEG\-CLOSE \- subscription_id
\&    NEG\-ERR   \- subscription_id, message (string), optional neg_limit (non\-negative integer)
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CW\*(C`subscription_id\*(C'\fR must be a non\-empty string of at most 64 characters
for REQ, CLOSE, and COUNT messages. For EOSE and CLOSED, subscription_id
must be defined but is not length\-validated (relay\-to\-client messages echo
back whatever the client sent). \f(CW\*(C`event_id\*(C'\fR must be 64\-character
lowercase hex. \f(CW\*(C`event\*(C'\fR must be a Net::Nostr::Event object.
\&\f(CW\*(C`filters\*(C'\fR must be an arrayref of Net::Nostr::Filter objects.
\&\f(CW\*(C`message\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`challenge\*(C'\fR must be non\-reference scalars.
.PP
For \f(CW\*(C`AUTH\*(C'\fR, passing both \f(CW\*(C`event\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`challenge\*(C'\fR is rejected. For
\&\f(CW\*(C`COUNT\*(C'\fR, passing both \f(CW\*(C`count\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`filters\*(C'\fR is rejected. Croaks on
missing required fields, invalid field formats, mutually exclusive
arguments, type mismatches, unknown type, or unknown arguments.
.SH METHODS
.IX Header "METHODS"
.SS serialize
.IX Subsection "serialize"
.Vb 1
\&    my $json = $msg\->serialize;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the JSON\-encoded message string per the NIP\-01 wire format.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->new(type => \*(AqCLOSE\*(Aq, subscription_id => \*(Aqx\*(Aq);
\&    say $msg\->serialize;  # \*(Aq["CLOSE","x"]\*(Aq
.Ve
.SS parse
.IX Subsection "parse"
.Vb 1
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->parse($json_string);
.Ve
.PP
Class method. Parses a JSON message string and returns a new
Net::Nostr::Message object. Croaks on invalid JSON, unknown message
types, or malformed messages. Validates structural format of each
message type (element count, field types). String fields
(subscription_id, message, challenge) are rejected if they are JSON
objects or arrays. \f(CW\*(C`event_id\*(C'\fR in OK messages must be 64\-character
lowercase hex. For EVENT and AUTH messages, the contained event is
constructed via \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Event\->from_wire\*(C'\fR which requires all
seven NIP\-01 fields (id, pubkey, created_at, kind, tags, content, sig)
and rejects missing or undefined fields.
.PP
\&\fBTrust boundary\fR: \f(CW\*(C`parse\*(C'\fR validates message structure and field formats
but does \fBnot\fR verify event signatures, event ID hashes, or
authenticity. The caller is responsible for verifying event integrity
via \f(CW\*(C`$event\->validate\*(C'\fR, which recomputes the ID hash and verifies
the signature against the event\*(Aqs own pubkey.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->parse(\*(Aq["NOTICE","hello"]\*(Aq);
\&    say $msg\->type;     # \*(AqNOTICE\*(Aq
\&    say $msg\->message;  # \*(Aqhello\*(Aq
.Ve
.SS type
.IX Subsection "type"
.Vb 1
\&    my $type = $msg\->type;  # \*(AqEVENT\*(Aq, \*(AqOK\*(Aq, \*(AqREQ\*(Aq, etc.
.Ve
.SS subscription_id
.IX Subsection "subscription_id"
.Vb 1
\&    my $sub_id = $msg\->subscription_id;
.Ve
.PP
The subscription ID. Present on EVENT (relay\-to\-client), REQ, CLOSE,
EOSE, and CLOSED messages.
.SS event
.IX Subsection "event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $event = $msg\->event;  # Net::Nostr::Event
.Ve
.PP
The event object. Present on EVENT and AUTH (client\-to\-relay) messages.
.SS event_id
.IX Subsection "event_id"
.Vb 1
\&    my $id = $msg\->event_id;
.Ve
.PP
The event ID string. Present on OK messages.
.SS accepted
.IX Subsection "accepted"
.Vb 1
\&    my $bool = $msg\->accepted;  # 1 or 0
.Ve
.PP
Whether the event was accepted. Present on OK messages.
.SS message
.IX Subsection "message"
.Vb 1
\&    my $text = $msg\->message;
.Ve
.PP
The message string. Present on OK, NOTICE, and CLOSED messages.
For OK and CLOSED, may include a machine\-readable prefix like
\&\f(CW"duplicate: already have this event"\fR.
.SS prefix
.IX Subsection "prefix"
.Vb 1
\&    my $prefix = $msg\->prefix;  # \*(Aqduplicate\*(Aq, \*(Aqblocked\*(Aq, etc. or undef
.Ve
.PP
The machine\-readable prefix extracted from the message string.
Standard prefixes: \f(CW\*(C`duplicate\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`pow\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`blocked\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`rate\-limited\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`invalid\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`restricted\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`auth\-required\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`mute\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`error\*(C'\fR.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->parse(
\&        \*(Aq["OK","aa...",false,"blocked: you are banned"]\*(Aq
\&    );
\&    say $msg\->prefix;  # \*(Aqblocked\*(Aq
.Ve
.SS count
.IX Subsection "count"
.Vb 1
\&    my $count = $msg\->count;  # non\-negative integer
.Ve
.PP
The event count. Present on COUNT response messages (NIP\-45). Must be
a non\-negative integer; croaks on references, non\-numeric strings,
negative values, or floats.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->parse(\*(Aq["COUNT","q1",{"count":42}]\*(Aq);
\&    say $msg\->count;  # 42
.Ve
.SS approximate
.IX Subsection "approximate"
.Vb 1
\&    my $approx = $msg\->approximate;  # 1 or undef
.Ve
.PP
Whether the count is probabilistic. Present on COUNT response messages
when the relay uses approximate counting.
.SS filters
.IX Subsection "filters"
.Vb 1
\&    my $filters = $msg\->filters;  # arrayref of Net::Nostr::Filter
.Ve
.PP
The filter objects. Present on REQ and COUNT (client\-to\-relay) messages.
.SS challenge
.IX Subsection "challenge"
.Vb 1
\&    my $challenge = $msg\->challenge;
.Ve
.PP
The challenge string. Present on AUTH messages from relays.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->parse(\*(Aq["AUTH","challenge123"]\*(Aq);
\&    say $msg\->challenge;  # \*(Aqchallenge123\*(Aq
.Ve
.SS neg_msg
.IX Subsection "neg_msg"
.Vb 1
\&    my $hex = $msg\->neg_msg;
.Ve
.PP
The negentropy protocol message as a hex string. Present on NEG\-OPEN
and NEG\-MSG messages.
.SS filter
.IX Subsection "filter"
.Vb 1
\&    my $filter = $msg\->filter;  # Net::Nostr::Filter
.Ve
.PP
A single NIP\-01 filter. Present on NEG\-OPEN messages.
.SS neg_limit
.IX Subsection "neg_limit"
.Vb 1
\&    my $limit = $msg\->neg_limit;  # non\-negative integer or undef
.Ve
.PP
Optional maximum number of records the relay will process. Present on
NEG\-ERR messages when the relay rejects a query as too large. Must be
a non\-negative integer; croaks on references, non\-numeric strings,
negative values, or floats.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Message\->parse(\*(Aq["NEG\-ERR","x","blocked: too big",100000]\*(Aq);
\&    say $msg\->neg_limit;  # 100000
.Ve
